3.2.1 UI Context Changes
If an action within a platform, app, or website will change the context of the user interface, that change must behave as users would expect.

3.2.1-A
A link must clearly communicate if it will change the context of the user interface.

3.2.1-B
User interface elements must not change based on an interaction without clearly notifying users of the change beforehand.

3.2.1-C
Changes of context must only be initiated by a direct user request. Changes of context by other methods must have a setting to enable or disable them.

3.2.1-D
Modals and dialogs must not force users to change context.
